50|$|The {{court system}} of Imperial Russia had {{remained}} intact since {{the reign of}} Catherine II. It included Estates-of-the-realm courts for different estates of the realm. Alexander II introduced a unified two-level system which consisted of General <b>judicial</b> <b>settlements</b> (Общие судебные установления) and Local <b>judicial</b> <b>settlements</b> (Местные судебные установления), where settlement (установление) stands for body or office. Courts were separated from the executive branch.|$|R
