40|$|What {{significance}} {{should one}} attribute to bankruptcies It is this simple {{question that the}} present article seeks to answer ft is based on examples of bankruptcies which occurred in Niort Deux-Sèvres between 1817 and 1874 and upon the liquidation of property and the <b>judicial</b> <b>settlements</b> declared at Nantes in 1974 Bankruptcies cannot provide us with an accurate picture of the economic situation of city or region during any given period {{just as they do}} not inform us of the real economic situation of ze merchant affected by this procedure Because of the modalities which govern these judicial and economic operations bankruptcies are to be seen {{in the context of the}} entire mercantile society its structure and the possibilities which if affords The phenomenon of bankruptcy is not reducible to one particular order of explanation but is an encompassing social factMartin Jean-Clément. Le commerçant, la faillite et l'historien. In: Annales. Économies, Sociétés, Civilisations. 35 ᵉ année, N. 6, 1980. pp. 1251 - 1268...|$|R
